      "name": "David W5DWD",
      "username": "dduffey",
      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/dduffey/{size}/5197_2.png",
      "created_at": "2024-01-03T18:07:32.103Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I noticed that the HR/Power chart between the Android and Web version don\u2019t use the same axis for Heart Rate.</p>\n<p>In particular, the Android version uses FTP and HR threshold as the \u201cmid point\u201d of the vertical axis (which is nice), but the Web Live View appears to default to 0 (min) \u2026110 (midpoint) \u2026220 (max).</p>\n<p>The android version I like \u201cbetter\u201d, but I think it could be improved as well.  Currently it is \u201c1/2 HRT\u201d \u2026 \u201cHRT\u201d \u2026 \u201c2x HRT\u201d \u2026 but \u201c2*\u201d HRT is too much, as you\u2019ll lever get a HR into the 300s.</p>\n<p>So, maybe both (Web Live View and App) could be:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Max: 220</li>\n<li>50% Mark: HRT</li>\n<li>Minimum: HRT - (220 - HRT), or 2*HRT - 220</li>\n</ul>\n<p>That would give scales like this<br>\n80 \u2026 150 \u2026 220<br>\n100 \u2026 160 \u2026 220</p>\n<p>And it seems like it would scale better as well (i.e. lower bound increases as LTHR increases with fitness, and as fitness increases \u201czooms\u201d in for a more nuanced view.</p>",
